A free six week peer-group program for founders

Hello Josh,

Under normal circumstances founders need a way to share the challenges of
entrepreneurship with other founders. But with the sudden onslaught of
COVID-related challenges, now more than ever, founders need support from
their peers.

To meet this need Betaworks Studios is launching a free beta version of a
new product we=E2=80=99re calling Circles
<https://betaworks-studios.us17.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dbe5801db019=
9500b845df659d&id=3D841e56ff24&e=3D8c52068cbb>
:* a 6-week, peer-to-peer mentorship program for curated cohorts of 8
founders and company leaders who meet regularly in mentor-led support
sessions.* For this first COVID-specific session, groups will meet
virtually once a week -- which means that you don't need to be in NYC to
participate. This product is open to anyone, not just Studios members.

Each Circles cohort will provide an intimate and confidential place for
founders to discuss and deal with challenges and opportunities of running a
startup during a crisis like COVID-19. *Circles is a safe place to have
real conversations*. It=E2=80=99s not just about networking, it=E2=80=99s a=
bout solving the
real, hard, human and business challenges you face.

Groups will be curated with facilitation by an experienced entrepreneur =E2=
=80=94
the initial mentor group includes: *Brian Donahue* (Director of Product
Engineering at Pinterest, former CEO, Instapaper), *Evan Lodge* (Head of
Product at NurseFly, YC Startup School Advisor), *Georg Petschnigg*
(General Manager, We Transfer, CEO, co-founder of FiftyThree, makers of
Paper), *Giordano Contestabile* (VP Product, IAC, former CEO of
Bloglovin), *Kyra
Reppen* (CEO, Katapult, former Viacom exec.), *Mark Josephson* (former CEO,
Bitly), *Beau Haugh* (former head of Product and Engineering at betaworks
Studios), *Upendra Shardanand* (founder RDF=C2=B0 Report, past founder Fire=
fly,
Accelerator Group, Daylife), *Madelin Woods* (CEO, Founder of Hello Walden)=
.

Applications
<https://betaworks-studios.us17.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dbe5801db019=
9500b845df659d&id=3Dd55e82117f&e=3D8c52068cbb>
to
join this special cohort of Circles are open now =E2=80=94 *the program is
completely free* if you are accepted. Participants will be considered on a
first-come-first-served basis until April 13, or until all of the spots are
filled.

*Go here to apply:* beta.works/circlesapp
<https://betaworks-studios.us17.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3Dbe5801db019=
9500b845df659d&id=3D55c6053105&e=3D8c52068cbb>

And whether or not you apply, please forward to anyone in your network who
you think is relevant and would be interested! We hope to help as many
people as we're able.

We will get through this, and we can be better together.

=E2=80=94 John Borthwick
